{"id":31864,"date":"2019-06-08T20:06:29","date_gmt":"2019-06-08T16:06:29","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=31864"},"modified":"2025-03-22T13:35:27","modified_gmt":"2025-03-22T09:35:27","slug":"sin-falls-on-the-instigator","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/08\/sin-falls-on-the-instigator\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Retaliation: Sin against instigator, unless he transgresses"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>If two people exchange harsh words, it is against the instigator as long as the one wronged does not transgress.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2587<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Muslim<\/p>\n<p>Imam al-Nawawi commented, \u201cIt means that the sin of using harsh words falls specifically and entirely on the instigator, unless the second person exceeds the limits of retaliation, such that he says to the instigator worse than what was said to him. In this is permission to retaliate, and there is no disagreement on its permission\u2026 But despite this, patience and forgiveness are better.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sharh\u0323 al-Nawawi\u0304 \u2018ala\u0301 S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 16\/141<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064f\u0633\u0652\u062a\u064e\u0628\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0646\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u06